<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4168.2.1>
    bibo:endPage "238" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "201" ;
    bibo:volume "4168" ;
    dc:creator "Klopfstein, Seraina" ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Revising Australian Pristomerus (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Cremastinae): species with a tooth on the hind femur" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375676>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375702>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375678>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375706> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375676>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Hind femur showing ventral tooth in Pristomerus bicinctus (A) and P. laetus (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/375676/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375702>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Second tergite being smooth and shining in Pristomerus bicinctus (A) and showing fine longitudinal carinulae in P. fourecksensis (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/375702/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375678>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Propodeum of (A) Pristomerus giraulti with complete juxacoxal carina and (B) of P. dundeei with only traces of the carina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/375678/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.375706>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Holotype of Pristomerus fourecksensis sp. nov. A. Habitus and ovipositor tip. B. Face. C. Mesoscutum and head from above. D. Head and mesosoma from lateral. E. Propodeum. F. Metasoma. Scale bars represent 1 mm (A) and 0.5 mm (B, C, D, E, F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/375706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

